  "body": "The Besu CLI has a sub command [generate-blockchain-config](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/Reference/CLI/CLI-Subcommands/#generate-blockchain-config) which generates the extraData field for the genesis files of IBFT2 networks.\r\n\r\nWith PR #2008 support for an alternative signature algorithm (secp256r1) has been added. But the `generate-blockchain-config` sub command is not aware of these changes and always uses the default secp256k1.  This generates an invalid extraData field if secp256r1 is supposed to be used.\r\n",
